etymologies: mid 17th century. From post-classical Latin planeticus wandering from Hellenistic Greek πλανητικός wandering, of or relating to a planet from ancient Greek πλανητός wandering, used occasionally of planets (from πλανᾶν to lead astray, in passive to wander + -τός, suffix forming verbal adjectives) + -ικός

definitions: Of, relating to, or caused by a planet or planets; = "planetary" 1b.
Of, relating to, or designating a dispersal stage in certain fungi and algae, involving motile cells or spores or (in later use) the transfer of nuclei between cells.
